I tried learning Klingon.

18:19.519 --> 18:21.886
- For me?
- Yeah.

18:21.921 --> 18:24.889
All I'm trying to say is...

18:24.924 --> 18:25.956
I love you.

18:25.992 --> 18:27.758
I know.

18:27.794 --> 18:29.760
Wait, are you quoting
the Carbonite scene

18:29.796 --> 18:30.828
from "Empire Strikes Back"?

18:30.863 --> 18:32.730
I am quoting the Carbonite scene

18:32.765 --> 18:33.931
from "Empire Strikes Back."

18:33.966 --> 18:36.434
Okay, that's the smile 'n' echo.

18:36.469 --> 18:38.636
<i>With that, me and Jackie were back.</i>

18:38.671 --> 18:41.472
<i>But for my brother,
love had no easy answer.</i>

18:41.507 --> 18:43.174
Hi, Mr. Ouija.

18:43.209 --> 18:44.608
I know this is asking a lot,

18:44.644 --> 18:46.477
but please,

18:46.512 --> 18:48.412
we need to know.

18:48.448 --> 18:50.181
Will we end up together?

18:51.584 --> 18:53.150
<i>Sometimes the hardest thing about love</i>

18:53.186 --> 18:56.187
<i>is realizing no one has all the answers.</i>

18:56.222 --> 18:57.822
I was really hoping it would work.

18:57.857 --> 18:59.657
Us, or the Ouija?

18:59.692 --> 19:00.858
Both.

19:03.096 --> 19:05.930
I'll always love you, Barry Goldberg.

19:05.965 --> 19:07.298
You know that, right?

19:13.072 --> 19:14.739
<i>Truth is,</i>

19:14.774 --> 19:17.208
<i>there's no trick to making
a relationship perfect.</i>

19:17.243 --> 19:18.743
Looks like you got through to them.

19:18.778 --> 19:19.977
Well done.

19:20.012 --> 19:22.279
Why do I feel so lousy?

19:22.315 --> 19:23.614
'Cause you were right.

19:23.649 --> 19:26.517
Long distance really does suck.

19:26.552 --> 19:27.818
But it's worth it.

19:27.854 --> 19:29.754
At least for us.

19:29.789 --> 19:31.322
And how can you be so sure?

19:37.330 --> 19:38.396
Does that answer your question?

19:38.431 --> 19:39.463
For sure. It's totally worth it.

19:40.633 --> 19:42.933
That towel takes up half the closet.

19:42.969 --> 19:44.468
You know what?

19:44.504 --> 19:45.636
I think it's growing on me.

19:47.874 --> 19:50.141
<i>Sure, there will always
be bumps along the way...</i>

19:50.176 --> 19:52.376
<i>...but when you find
that perfect person...</i>

19:52.412 --> 19:54.445
<i>there's nothing better in the universe.</i>

19:54.480 --> 19:57.415
Adam: Admit it. You like
"Star Wars" a little.

19:57.450 --> 19:58.849
These buns are kind of growing on me.

20:01.888 --> 20:11.862
_

20:17.799 --> 20:19.905
<i>Okay, we've been through this a lot.</i>

20:20.142 --> 20:22.401
I just... I want you to
relax, just be in the moment,

20:22.587 --> 20:23.837
and for the love of God,

20:24.006 --> 20:25.598
act like you've been there.

20:25.634 --> 20:26.733
Which I have.

20:26.768 --> 20:28.234
So, it's so strange
that I keep acting like

20:28.270 --> 20:29.302
I have yet to be there.

20:29.337 --> 20:31.004
Bad start. Here we go.

20:34.709 --> 20:35.809
That's an A+.

20:35.844 --> 20:37.277
4.0 GPA!

20:37.312 --> 20:38.778
Hittin' the books, makin' the grades!

20:40.148 --> 20:41.181
That is some quality craftsmanship.

20:41.216 --> 20:42.348
Hand sewn!

20:42.384 --> 20:43.716
Rich Corinthian leather!

20:44.186 --> 20:45.351
Great stuff, fine work.

20:45.387 --> 20:46.586
Not work, play.

20:46.621 --> 20:49.022
All work and no play
makes Adam a dull boy.

20:50.625 --> 20:52.091
Hello, Nurse!

20:52.127 --> 20:53.927
The doctor's in!

20:53.962 --> 20:55.662
Your prescription's ready!

20:55.697 --> 20:56.696
You know what?

20:56.731 --> 21:01.291
- Let's just pick this back up tomorrow?
- That seems reasonable.

